Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1382/91 of 21 May 1991 on the submission of data on the landings of fishery products in the Member States (1), and in particular Article 5 (3) and (4) thereof,
Whereas the existing programme of fishery statistics in Italy requires modification in order to fully meet the provisions of the abovementioned Regulation;
Whereas the collection of data on the landings of fishery products by more than 20 000 fishing vessels in the numerous ports and landing places along the 8 000 km of Italian coastline imposes particular difficulties in establishing the modified  statistical system;
Whereas the Italian Republic has requested a partial derogation from the provisions of the abovementioned Regulation;
Whereas the measures foreseen by the present Decision conform to the opinion of the Standing Committee for Agricultural Statistics,
